1
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:09,973
[Episode 2: Please, Mr. Drizzle]

2
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:13,280
<i>Raise the hand on the side where you hear.</i>

3
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:14,280
<i>Understand?</i>

4
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:15,079
Yes.

5
00:01:15,079 --> 00:01:16,519
<i>Okay. The hearing test begins.</i>

6
00:01:16,519 --> 00:01:18,359
<i>In life,</i>

7
00:01:18,359 --> 00:01:20,599
<i>we are faced with countless choices.</i>

8
00:01:20,599 --> 00:01:21,680
<i>Left</i>

9
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,239
<i>or right?</i>

10
00:01:23,239 --> 00:01:24,640
<i>Love</i>

11
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:26,260
<i>or hate?</i>

12
00:01:26,879 --> 00:01:28,040
<i>- Dad</i>
- It's because of you!

13
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:29,508
<i>or Mom?</i>

14
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,439
Who would know in advance?

15
00:01:31,439 --> 00:01:33,280
- You...
- The doctor said

16
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:34,680
his left ear

17
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,040
has sudden deafness.

18
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:37,120
You're his mom.

19
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:39,000
If you don't take care of him, who will?

20
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,519
So? He isn't your son?

21
00:01:41,519 --> 00:01:44,131
You ignore him after divorce?

22
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,121
What nonsense!

23
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:49,239
You ignore him?

24
00:01:49,239 --> 00:01:49,840
So do I.

25
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:51,519
<i>- From this day on,</i>
- Up to you.

26
00:01:51,519 --> 00:01:53,000
<i>- I no longer make a choice easily.</i>
- Who cares, who takes care.

27
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:57,000
They say I'm unwanted.

28
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,239
Forget it.

29
00:01:58,239 --> 00:01:59,760
Let's go home.

30
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:01,280
<i>Faced with a problem,</i>

31
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:04,280
<i>I keep checking and proving,</i>

32
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:07,359
<i>don't answer until I'm sure</i>

33
00:02:07,359 --> 00:02:08,759
<i>it's correct.</i>

34
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:10,599
Black or white?

35
00:02:10,599 --> 00:02:14,880
The different steps out.

36
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:16,969
Ren Xi Zhou is it. Hide!

37
00:02:17,599 --> 00:02:18,520
Ten,

38
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:19,560
nine,

39
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:21,080
eight,

40
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:22,319
seven,

41
00:02:22,319 --> 00:02:23,649
six...

42
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,199
<i>No one came looking for me.</i>

43
00:02:40,199 --> 00:02:41,639
<i>They have gone home.</i>

44
00:02:41,639 --> 00:02:43,720
<i>I didn't want to see them again,</i>

45
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:46,000
<i>especially Ren Xi Zhou.</i>

46
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,195
<i>But it backfired.</i>

47
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,760
<i>I stood in the corner,</i>

48
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:54,749
<i>forced to admire her glamorous life</i>

49
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,144
[Ren Xi Zhou]
<i>until...</i>

50
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:00,535
<i>today.</i>

51
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,603
It's been a while.

52
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:17,440
My friend left something

53
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:18,759
at your stall.

54
00:03:18,759 --> 00:03:20,199
She returned but couldn't find it.

55
00:03:20,199 --> 00:03:21,440
So she asked me for a favor.

56
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:22,520
You have a friend

57
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,319
who knows me?

58
00:03:24,319 --> 00:03:25,520
It's a grocery cart

59
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:27,140
with vegetables inside.

60
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:32,369
Excuse me.

61
00:03:33,734 --> 00:03:34,759
Hey!

62
00:03:34,759 --> 00:03:37,002
[Watermelon Yard]
You treat guests this way?

63
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:40,080
Well,

64
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:42,920
worse temper after years of departure.

65
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:45,360
Hey, Xiang Nan Feng.

66
00:03:46,919 --> 00:03:48,193
Hey,

67
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:53,919
it's all in the past.

68
00:03:53,919 --> 00:03:56,599
Give it back to me.

69
00:03:56,599 --> 00:03:58,360
Hey, Xiang Nan Feng!

70
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,914
Open the door!

71
00:04:01,719 --> 00:04:02,759
Believe it or not,

72
00:04:02,759 --> 00:04:04,710
I'll take all your vegetables!

73
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:14,599
<i>Burning charcoal in summer</i>

74
00:04:14,599 --> 00:04:15,960
<i>with the door closed?</i>

75
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,879
<i>Is he poisoned?</i>

76
00:04:17,879 --> 00:04:19,640
Xiang Nan Feng!

77
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:21,120
Are you okay?

78
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:22,552
Xiang Nan Feng!

79
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,792
Xiang Nan Feng!

80
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:31,839
<i>Just an ex who seems to live well.</i>

81
00:04:31,839 --> 00:04:33,642
<i>Do you have to do this?</i>

82
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,342
[Let Go Yard]
Xiang Nan Feng!

83
00:04:50,079 --> 00:04:52,160
Xiang Nan Feng, are you alright?

84
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,256
Open the door, Xiang Nan Feng!

85
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:02,400
<i>Are you okay?</i>

86
00:05:14,759 --> 00:05:16,600
Xiang Nan Feng!

87
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,935
Are you okay, Xiang Nan Feng?

88
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:25,329
Xiang Nan Feng!

89
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,655
Xiang Nan Feng!

90
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:30,177
Xiang Nan Feng!

91
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,882
Give me a stool.

92
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,700
What?

93
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,920
Please

94
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,945
give me a stool.

95
00:06:06,839 --> 00:06:09,089
Why didn't you reply since you're alright?

96
00:06:09,879 --> 00:06:11,759
Based on the size of the kitchen,

97
00:06:11,759 --> 00:06:12,759
the generation rate

98
00:06:12,759 --> 00:06:15,199
and concentration of carbon monoxide

99
00:06:15,199 --> 00:06:17,058
aren't an immediate danger.

100
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,399
Well,

101
00:06:19,399 --> 00:06:20,399
how are you?

102
00:06:20,399 --> 00:06:21,830
Let's skip the formalities.

103
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,360
When did you return?

104
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,639
Since we broke up,

105
00:06:25,639 --> 00:06:27,142
I've been working here.

106
00:06:34,879 --> 00:06:36,519
As a grocer?

107
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:37,796
Scriptwriter.

108
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,450
Nice station.

109
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:46,120
But too desolate

110
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:49,447
to know Nanwan is called Florida.

111
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,840
I drop by from a trip

112
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:55,693
to visit my mom.

113
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:59,240
It's 80 km from the nearest airport.

114
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,643
You drop by.

115
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,440
But...

116
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:09,425
How did you know I was in Florida?

117
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:18,022
You don't follow me.

118
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,941
I heard it.

119
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,934
From whom?

120
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:34,777
The food's at the door.

121
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,600
How about my cart?

122
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,420
I couldn't bring it when riding home.

123
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,439
Besides,

124
00:07:49,439 --> 00:07:51,360
isn't that your friend's?

125
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,763
None of your...

126
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,283
business.

127
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,240
Fragrant stuffed buns.

128
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:03,879
Thank you.

129
00:08:03,879 --> 00:08:05,360
- What filling?
- Seafood.

130
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,040
Delicious?

131
00:08:14,625 --> 00:08:15,759
Cheapskate.

132
00:08:15,759 --> 00:08:16,920
I was worried about you.

133
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:18,798
Just a stuffed bun.

134
00:08:25,133 --> 00:08:26,199
For you.

135
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:27,399
We're even.

136
00:08:27,399 --> 00:08:28,760
I'm well since we parted ways.

137
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:31,865
So, please don't disturb a cheapskate.

138
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,600
Don't worry. I won't.

139
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,041
I'm leaving soon.

140
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:43,104
Besides, I'm better off than you.

141
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:15,500
Pretty good.

142
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,562
The stuffed buns are delicious.

143
00:09:59,279 --> 00:10:01,080
If you don't mind,

144
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:04,320
please tell me the recipe.

145
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:07,240
I'll pay for it.

146
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,540
Thank you.

147
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:19,000
I just want to improve the menu

148
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,320
with your recipe,

149
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:23,400
not to disturb you.

150
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,170
<i>Deleted me?</i>

151
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:55,227
What are you looking at?

152
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:06,520
Hello?

153
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,200
<i>Hi, Mr. Xiang,</i>

154
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,279
<i>the producer and I read</i>

155
00:11:09,279 --> 00:11:10,799
<i>the draft of the first three episodes.</i>

156
00:11:10,799 --> 00:11:14,039
<i>I hear it's your first romance script.</i>

157
00:11:14,039 --> 00:11:16,080
Cut to the point.

158
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:18,440
<i>Your style and rhythm are impeccable.</i>

159
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,080
<i>But the content seems</i>

160
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,799
<i>irrelevant to people's impression</i>

161
00:11:21,799 --> 00:11:23,159
<i>of first love.</i>

162
00:11:23,159 --> 00:11:24,960
<i>Think about how you</i>

163
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:27,080
<i>felt in your first love.</i>

164
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,741
Ridiculous?

165
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:32,392
<i>Well, could you please alter it?</i>

166
00:11:32,392 --> 00:11:34,880
<i>Recall your feeling in first love</i>

167
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:36,190
<i>and...</i>

168
00:11:42,039 --> 00:11:44,879
In high school, you still don't study hard.

169
00:11:44,879 --> 00:11:46,600
You cheated

170
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,880
and passed the buck to Xiang Nan Feng?

171
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:51,277
Don't you know the classroom is monitored?

172
00:12:14,559 --> 00:12:15,960
It stinks.

173
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:18,000
Where's it from?

174
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,039
Let's go.

175
00:12:19,039 --> 00:12:20,284
It's going to rain.

176
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:34,726
Did you hear?

177
00:12:34,726 --> 00:12:36,600
Xiang Nan Feng smells like poop.

178
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,620
It's said he fertilizes every day.

179
00:12:38,620 --> 00:12:39,720
It's disgusting.

180
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:41,497
Do you smell something?

181
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,480
The cinema opened last week.

182
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:47,240
You haven't been there yet?

183
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,580
My dad even asked his secretary

184
00:12:48,580 --> 00:12:50,030
to drive me there.

185
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,130
Too crowded.

186
00:12:52,759 --> 00:12:54,879
My dad and his secretary are too busy

187
00:12:54,879 --> 00:12:57,064
to line up and buy tickets for me.

188
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,840
Actually my dad is busy too.

189
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:00,880
But I fawned,

190
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,283
and he agreed.

191
00:13:02,283 --> 00:13:03,298
Oh.

192
00:13:11,294 --> 00:13:13,652
Oh, it stinks.

193
00:13:17,559 --> 00:13:19,100
What are you doing?

194
00:13:27,519 --> 00:13:30,519
- Coward.
- He doesn't stink, Chao.

195
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:32,320
Are you sure?

196
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:34,057
You can ask!

197
00:13:35,799 --> 00:13:37,103
Do you smell it?

198
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:39,021
No.

199
00:13:41,639 --> 00:13:43,280
Maybe a little.

200
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:46,120
Right. It stinks.

201
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:48,713
Xiang Nan Feng fertilizes every day.

202
00:13:48,713 --> 00:13:50,548
He stinks.

203
00:13:51,927 --> 00:13:53,554
Do you smell it?

204
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:56,631
I'll break your fingers.

205
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:01,607
So what if your dad is rich?

206
00:14:23,420 --> 00:14:25,720
Analyzed syntactically...

207
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,200
They gave it to me willingly. What can I do?

208
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,020
It's incomplete.

209
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:29,240
I didn't rob them.

210
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:30,516
It needs a...

211
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,080
It's incomplete,

212
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:38,034
so A and B are excluded?

213
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:57,760
<i>I didn't smell the stink they said.</i>

214
00:14:57,760 --> 00:14:59,921
<i>Yet I couldn't help but doubt myself.</i>

215
00:15:00,519 --> 00:15:02,376
<i>Like Pavlov's dog,</i>

216
00:15:03,159 --> 00:15:05,279
<i>whenever someone frowned,</i>

217
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:07,427
<i>I examined myself like a reflex.</i>

218
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:21,759
Give it back to me!

219
00:15:21,759 --> 00:15:23,480
Let's go. He didn't do it on purpose.

220
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,639
- Give it to me!
- A shoe that's stepped on poop.

221
00:15:25,639 --> 00:15:26,840
Do you want to see it?

222
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:27,879
It's not good.

223
00:15:27,879 --> 00:15:29,640
The headmaster comes for class skippers.

224
00:15:29,640 --> 00:15:30,641
Go!

225
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,560
Excuse me.

226
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:17,800
Sorry. I'll call you tomorrow.

227
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,612
I know you're awake.

228
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:26,600
Is a favor disturbing?

229
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,310
- Yes.
- No.

230
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:35,240
To disturb means

231
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:37,951
to bother others by either word or act.

232
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:41,392
Excuse me.

233
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,661
Can I borrow an umbrella?
